ide test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |\n \n **Sprint 5 total:** ~27 hrs\n \n@@ -83,20 +78,18 @@\n \n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\n-| 38 | T-038 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCH-032 | — | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\n-| 39 | T-039 | Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. | T2 | 4 | 6 | CCH-038 | — | - offline renderer produces 5-minute proxy audio for fixture pieces<br/>- librosa self-similarity matrix + Foote novelty curve extracted<br/>- symbolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |\n-| 40 | T-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCH-040 | — | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\n+| 33 | T-033 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | T2